    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_405921">I'm looking for ideas on how to make the all-powerful Ring of Sustenance not so munchkin-y.<br />
 <br />
For those that don't know the object in question, it pretty much allows the wearer a pretty much permanent effect of <i>complete</i> freedom from hunger and thirst; as well as making them only need 2 hours of sleep vs. the normal 8 (or elves' 4). <br />
 <br />
The only limitation the ring currently has is that it takes a full week after you put it on for it to take effect, and it costs 2,500 gp. If you take off the ring, it takes another full week for the ring to start working again.<br />
 <br />
My ideas thus far were to make the effect not one of complete abatment of the need to eat and drink. <font face="Arial"><font size="3"><font face="Verdana"><font size="2">Instead of needing to eat and drink, say, once a day, it may be every 4 days or so. Or maybe it only works for a certain amount of time and needs to be removed for a short period of time to ‘recharge’ its energies, which would typically be done when the characters are back in a settled area.</font></font></font></font><br />
 <br />
<font face="Arial"><font size="3"><font face="Verdana"><font size="2">It's difficult to not allow the item at all, because this is an Underdark campaign, and even though the characters will all start at level 9, the Underdark can be as unforgiving as a desert when it comes to obtaining food and water.</font></font><br />
<br />
</font></font></div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
