    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_405930">This is my first campaign.  I've been wanting to do an Underdark campaign for a while now, and finally, having put EQ to the side, have the time to actually get one together.  It's a total new experience for me.  I wanted to include some local color by coming up with foods and drinks for the PC's while in town, and things that they might forage in the wilds, but if they don't <b>need</b> to eat or drink at all, I forsee the players not ever doing such.<br />
 <br />
In the other campaign being run by another in our group, we have to buy meals when we're in town, and eat our trail rations or forage for food (we had a lot of rangers and druids in the party) when out on the road.  There's this one guy that always forgets to mark off that he's eaten something, or has shot an arrow, or used some other expendable item.  He's also a good one for munchkin-ing his characters to the max. <img src="images/smilies/emote_wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /></div>
