    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_406096">Doon has the key on spellcasters. Just because you only need 2 hours of sleep doesn't mean you don't need more for spells.<br />
<br />
Also, if everyone in your group is buying this item, why would you ever allow it to be that commonly available? Is there a magic item shop with infinite inventory? Because of the xp cost on making magic items, there should almost never be an overstock of magic lying around to be purchased, unless you're in Sigil.<br />
<br />
Remember, the primary purchasers of magical goods are adventurers. Availability should be offset by demand. And base price doesn't include other factors.<br />
<br />
Magical items require a skill practitioner to craft, rare components, and experience points. If the PC's want a magic item made, make them do some legwork for whatever mage is making the item.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
