    <div align="left" id="post_message_406152">Well, the party is going to be made up of mostly rogues and rangers... I allowed people to play whatever class they wanted, rather than saying &quot;well, we need a cleric...&quot;, so I'm slightly more willing to let them have magical trinkets and whatnot to fill in for the lack of wizards, sorcerers, druids, and clerics.<br />
 <br />
The city that the characters are starting out in is a trade city, and just about everything is available... for a price.  I've already warned them that some stuff might cost more than the standard rulebook cost, or be unavailable.  They're starting out with 50K gold, and are not allowed spend all of it on one item, lest they be running around nekkid. <img src="images/smilies/emote_wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /></div>
