	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_406300">In my experience, starting a party at higher level results in one of three undesired outcomes.<br />
<br />
1) Everyone knows their class well and min/maxes to the point where they can stomp level appropriate content, thereby ruining your carefully crafted campaign.<br />
<br />
2) People don't know their class well and are gimped, plus take forever during gameplay to figure out what the 'right' response is to a given scenario.<br />
<br />
3) You get a mix of 1 and 2 such that part of the party is having fun overpowering content while the other part is sulking because they don't get to do anything.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
