    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_406455">I've instituted the following rules to help keep from being too overbalanced in the equipment dept.<br />
 <br />
<font face="Arial">50K purchase limit</font><br />
<br />
<font face="Arial">There will be a limit of +2 on enhancement bonuses on items such as weapons, shields, and armor.   This includes +1/Keen which is effectively a +2 weapon.</font><br />
<br />
<font face="Arial">Items with permanent or triggered spell effects with no # of charges will be capped at caster level 5, unless you’re able to craft the item yourself.  Does not include MOST wands, potions, oils, scrolls, elixirs, dusts, ointments &amp; salves, feather tokens, and other items with one use or a # of charges.  Of course, I retain the right to approve all items.</font><br />
<br />
<font face="Arial">Not included in this limit are Bag of Holding Type I and Type II; Handy Haversack; Efficient Quiver; Bracers of Armor +1; or Folding Boat.  I’ll also allow Gloves of Storing, just because I’m a rogue at heart.</font><br />
<br />
<font face="Arial">Here’s a list of magical items that are allowed.  Any other items are up to DM approval.</font><br />
<br />
<font face="Arial">    * Rings : <div style="margin:5px 20px 20px 20px">

<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>SPOILER:</b>

