<br />
<br />
<font face="Arial">Mithril and Adamantite weapons, shields, and armor are OK, and in fact, encouraged – armors such as Mithral Shirt, Adamantine Breastplate, Dwarven Plate, Elven Chain, Mithral Heavy Shield may also have additional bonuses and effects added.</font><br />
<br />
<font face="Arial">Remember that you can only use/wear a certain number of items at one time – however, you can own any number of items and swap them in and out as situations require.  You only may only have 2 rings active at one time, but you can wear multiple rings that have different triggered effects. </font><br />
<br />
<font face="Arial">Keep in mind that the Ring of Sustenance takes up a slot that could be used for a more useful effect.  Food isn’t scarce in the area that you’ll be in.</font><br />
<br />
<font face="Arial">You don’t need to spend every penny of the 50K limit, in fact, it might be a good idea to have some liquid cash reserves just in case you need to pay for fines, fees, bribes, entertainment, etc.  Banking and coin conversion are readily available in the city.</font></div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
<br>
<table width="100%%"  border="0" cellpadding="3">
<tr>
<td>


</td>
 </tr>
</table>
 

</div>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

